COD SETUP:


1. Configure, make and make install cercs_env.
2. Configure, make and make install atl.
3. Configure, make and make install ffs/fm.
4. Configure, make and make install dill.
5. Configure, make and make install ffs/cod.
6. Make sure atl.h, cercs_env.h, cod.h, dill.h, dill_internal.h and fm.h have been copied to /usr/local/include.
7. Make sure LD_LIBRARY_PATH is set to /usr/local/lib.

Now building ocelot will correctly link with the cod dependencies.

This sequence of commands executed in the /lynx directory should accomplish steps 1-5 above:

	cd cercs_env; ./configure && make && sudo make install; cd ..
	cd alt; ./configure && make && sudo make install; cd ..
	cd ffs/ffm; ./configure && make && sudo make install; cd ../..
	cd dill; ./configure && make && sudo make install; cd ..
	cd ffs/cod; ./configure && make && sudo make install; cd ../..

